<file path="docs/BEST_PRACTICES.md">
  1: # Best Practices for Schema.org in File Management
  2: 
  3: This guide provides best practices for using Schema.org structured data in file organization and management systems.
  4: 
  5: ## Table of Contents
  6: 
  7: 1. [Schema Selection](#schema-selection)
  8: 2. [Property Guidelines](#property-guidelines)
  9: 3. [Validation Strategy](#validation-strategy)
 10: 4. [Performance Optimization](#performance-optimization)
 11: 5. [Integration Patterns](#integration-patterns)
 12: 6. [Common Pitfalls](#common-pitfalls)
 13: 
 14: ---
 15: 
 16: ## Schema Selection
 17: 
 18: ### Choose the Most Specific Type
 19: 
 20: Always use the most specific Schema.org type available:
 21: 
 22: **Good:**
 23: ```python
 24: # Use specific type for research paper
 25: doc = DocumentGenerator("ScholarlyArticle")
 26: ```
 27: 
 28: **Bad:**
 29: ```python
 30: # Using generic type
 31: doc = DocumentGenerator("CreativeWork")
 32: ```
 33: 
 34: ### Type Hierarchy
 35: 
 36: Understand the Schema.org type hierarchy:
 37: 
 38: ```
 39: Thing
 40: └── CreativeWork
 41:     ├── Article
 42:     │   ├── NewsArticle
 43:     │   ├── BlogPosting
 44:     │   └── ScholarlyArticle
 45:     ├── DigitalDocument
 46:     │   └── (Your files)
 47:     ├── MediaObject
 48:     │   ├── ImageObject
 49:     │   │   └── Photograph
 50:     │   ├── VideoObject
 51:     │   └── AudioObject
 52:     │       ├── MusicRecording
 53:     │       └── PodcastEpisode
 54:     ├── SoftwareSourceCode
 55:     └── Dataset
 56: ```
 57: 
 58: ### File Type Mapping
 59: 
 60: | File Extension | Primary Type | Alternative Types |
 61: |---------------|-------------|-------------------|
 62: | .pdf | DigitalDocument | Article, Report, ScholarlyArticle |
 63: | .jpg, .png | ImageObject | Photograph |
 64: | .mp4, .mov | VideoObject | MovieClip |
 65: | .mp3, .wav | AudioObject | MusicRecording, PodcastEpisode |
 66: | .py, .js | SoftwareSourceCode | - |
 67: | .csv, .json | Dataset | - |
 68: | .zip, .tar | DigitalDocument | Archive |
 69: 
 70: ---
 71: 
 72: ## Property Guidelines
 73: 
 74: ### Required vs Recommended
 75: 
 76: Always include required properties, aim for recommended properties:
 77: 
 78: ```python
 79: # Required properties (will fail validation)
 80: doc.set_property("name", "Document Title")
 81: doc.set_property("encodingFormat", "application/pdf")
 82: 
 83: # Recommended properties (improves quality)
 84: doc.add_person("author", "Jane Smith")
 85: doc.set_dates(created=datetime.now())
 86: doc.add_keywords(["topic1", "topic2"])
 87: ```
 88: 
 89: ### URL Best Practices
 90: 
 91: **Always use absolute URLs:**
 92: 
 93: ```python
 94: # Good - Absolute URL
 95: doc.set_property("url", "https://example.com/file.pdf")
 96: 
 97: # Bad - Relative URL
 98: doc.set_property("url", "/files/file.pdf")
 99: 
100: # Good - File URL for local files
101: doc.set_property("url", "file:///path/to/file.pdf")
102: ```
103: 
104: ### Date Formats
105: 
106: Use ISO 8601 format for all dates:
107: 
108: ```python
109: # Good - ISO 8601
110: doc.set_dates(
111:     created=datetime(2024, 1, 15, 10, 30, 0),
112:     published=datetime(2024, 1, 20)
113: )
114: 
115: # Result: "2024-01-15T10:30:00" and "2024-01-20"
116: ```
117: 
118: ### Duration Format
119: 
120: Use ISO 8601 duration format:
121: 
122: ```python
123: # Good examples
124: video.set_property("duration", "PT5M30S")  # 5 minutes 30 seconds
125: video.set_property("duration", "PT1H30M")  # 1 hour 30 minutes
126: audio.set_property("duration", "PT3M45S")  # 3 minutes 45 seconds
127: 
128: # Helper method
129: def seconds_to_iso_duration(seconds: int) -> str:
130:     hours = seconds // 3600
131:     minutes = (seconds % 3600) // 60
132:     secs = seconds % 60
133:     return f"PT{hours}H{minutes}M{secs}S" if hours else f"PT{minutes}M{secs}S"
134: ```
135: 
136: ### Keywords and Tags
137: 
138: Be specific and use consistent terminology:
139: 
140: ```python
141: # Good - Specific, consistent keywords
142: doc.add_keywords([
143:     "machine learning",
144:     "neural networks",
145:     "artificial intelligence"
146: ])
147: 
148: # Bad - Too generic, inconsistent
149: doc.add_keywords([
150:     "ML",  # Use full term
151:     "AI stuff",  # Too vague
152:     "Neural Networks",  # Inconsistent capitalization
153: ])
154: ```
