<file path="docs/TIMELINE_INTEGRATION.md">
  1: # Timeline Integration Guide
  2: 
  3: Quick guide to connecting the timeline visualization to your actual database.
  4: 
  5: ## Setup Steps
  6: 
  7: ### 1. Generate Timeline Data
  8: 
  9: ```bash
 10: # From project root
 11: python3 src/api/timeline_api.py --db-path results/file_organization.db --output _site/timeline_data.json
 12: ```
 13: 
 14: **Expected Output**:
 15: ```
 16: ✅ Timeline data exported successfully to _site/timeline_data.json
 17: 
 18: 📊 Summary:
 19:    Total Sessions: 17
 20:    Total Files: 30,133
 21:    Success Rate: 98.6%
 22:    Total Cost: $45.23
 23: ```
 24: 
 25: ### 2. Update Timeline HTML to Use Real Data
 26: 
 27: Edit `/Users/alyshialedlie/schema-org-file-system/_site/timeline.html` and replace the `loadSessionData()` function:
 28: 
 29: ```javascript
 30: async function loadSessionData() {
 31:     try {
 32:         // Fetch from generated JSON file
 33:         const response = await fetch('timeline_data.json');
 34:         const data = await response.json();
 35: 
 36:         sessions = data.sessions;
 37: 
 38:         renderTimeline();
 39:         updateHeaderStats();
 40: 
 41:         document.getElementById('loadingState').style.display = 'none';
 42:         document.getElementById('timelineContainer').style.display = 'block';
 43:     } catch (error) {
 44:         console.error('Failed to load session data:', error);
 45:         document.getElementById('loadingState').innerHTML = `
 46:             <div class="empty-state">
 47:                 <div class="empty-state-icon">⚠️</div>
 48:                 <h2>Failed to load data</h2>
 49:                 <p>${error.message}</p>
 50:                 <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 1rem;">
 51:                     Make sure you've generated timeline data:<br>
 52:                     <code style="background: var(--dark-card); padding: 0.5rem; border-radius: 0.25rem; display: inline-block; margin-top: 0.5rem;">
 53:                         python3 src/api/timeline_api.py
 54:                     </code>
 55:                 </p>
 56:                 <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="loadSessionData()" style="margin-top: 1rem;">Retry</button>
 57:             </div>
 58:         `;
 59:     }
 60: }
 61: ```
 62: 
 63: ### 3. Serve the Timeline Locally
 64: 
 65: ```bash
 66: # Option 1: Python simple server
 67: cd _site
 68: python3 -m http.server 8000
 69: 
 70: # Option 2: Node.js http-server (if installed)
 71: npx http-server _site -p 8000
 72: 
 73: # Then open: http://localhost:8000/timeline.html
 74: ```
 75: 
 76: ## CLI Usage
 77: 
 78: ### Get All Sessions
 79: ```bash
 80: python3 src/api/timeline_api.py
 81: ```
 82: 
 83: ### Get Specific Session
 84: ```bash
 85: python3 src/api/timeline_api.py --session-id "session-uuid-here"
 86: ```
 87: 
 88: ### Compare Two Sessions
 89: ```bash
 90: python3 src/api/timeline_api.py --compare session-1 session-2
 91: ```
 92: 
 93: ### Show Aggregate Statistics
 94: ```bash
 95: python3 src/api/timeline_api.py --stats
 96: ```
 97: 
 98: **Output Example**:
 99: ```json
100: {
101:   "total_sessions": 17,
102:   "total_files_processed": 30133,
103:   "total_organized": 29703,
104:   "total_errors": 142,
105:   "total_cost": 45.23,
106:   "average_success_rate": 98.6,
107:   "category_breakdown": {
108:     "GameAssets": 25567,
109:     "Photos": 2450,
110:     "Documents": 1850,
111:     "Legal": 266
112:   },
113:   "dry_run_count": 3,
114:   "live_run_count": 14
115: }
116: ```
117: 
118: ## Automation
119: 
120: ### Auto-Generate After Each Run
121: 
122: Add this to your file organizer script:
123: 
124: ```python
125: from src.api.timeline_api import TimelineAPI
126: 
127: # After organization completes
128: api = TimelineAPI('results/file_organization.db')
129: api.export_to_json('_site/timeline_data.json')
130: print("Timeline data updated!")
131: ```
132: 
133: ### Scheduled Refresh
134: 
135: Create a cron job to regenerate timeline data:
136: 
137: ```bash
138: # Edit crontab
139: crontab -e
140: 
141: # Add this line (updates every hour)
142: 0 * * * * cd /Users/alyshialedlie/schema-org-file-system && python3 src/api/timeline_api.py > /dev/null 2>&1
143: ```
144: 
145: ## Flask API (Optional)
146: 
147: For real-time data, create a Flask endpoint:
148: 
149: ```python
150: # src/api/flask_server.py
151: from flask import Flask, jsonify
152: from flask_cors import CORS
153: from timeline_api import TimelineAPI
154: 
155: app = Flask(__name__)
156: CORS(app)
157: 
158: api = TimelineAPI('results/file_organization.db')
159: 
160: @app.route('/api/sessions')
161: def get_sessions():
162:     """Get all sessions."""
163:     return jsonify(api.get_all_sessions())
164: 
165: @app.route('/api/sessions/<session_id>')
166: def get_session(session_id):
167:     """Get specific session."""
168:     session = api.get_session_by_id(session_id)
169:     if session:
170:         return jsonify(session)
171:     return jsonify({'error': 'Session not found'}), 404
172: 
173: @app.route('/api/sessions/compare/<id1>/<id2>')
174: def compare_sessions(id1, id2):
175:     """Compare two sessions."""
176:     comparison = api.get_session_comparison(id1, id2)
177:     return jsonify(comparison)
178: 
179: @app.route('/api/stats')
180: def get_stats():
181:     """Get aggregate statistics."""
182:     return jsonify(api.get_aggregate_stats())
183: 
184: if __name__ == '__main__':
185:     app.run(debug=True, port=5000)
186: ```
187: 
188: **Install dependencies**:
189: ```bash
190: pip install flask flask-cors
191: ```
192: 
193: **Run server**:
194: ```bash
195: python3 src/api/flask_server.py
196: ```
197: 
198: **Update timeline.html**:
199: ```javascript
200: // Change fetch URL
201: const response = await fetch('http://localhost:5000/api/sessions');
202: ```
203: 
204: ## Troubleshooting
205: 
206: ### Database Not Found
207: ```
208: ❌ Error: Database not found: results/file_organization.db
209: ```
210: 
211: **Solution**: Run the file organizer at least once to create the database:
212: ```bash
213: python3 scripts/file_organizer_content_based.py --dry-run --limit 10
214: ```
215: 
216: ### No Sessions in Database
217: ```json
218: {
219:   "sessions": [],
220:   "aggregate_stats": {
221:     "total_sessions": 0
222:   }
223: }
224: ```
225: 
226: **Solution**: Check if `organization_sessions` table has data:
227: ```bash
228: sqlite3 results/file_organization.db "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM organization_sessions;"
229: ```
230: 
231: ### CORS Errors in Browser
232: ```
233: Access to fetch at 'file:///...' from origin 'null' has been blocked by CORS policy
234: ```
235: 
236: **Solution**: Use a local server instead of opening file directly:
237: ```bash
238: python3 -m http.server 8000 -d _site
239: ```
240: 
241: ### Old Data Showing
242: ```
243: Timeline shows old sessions that were deleted
244: ```
245: 
246: **Solution**: Regenerate timeline data:
247: ```bash
248: python3 src/api/timeline_api.py
249: # Then hard refresh in browser (Cmd+Shift+R)
250: ```
251: 
252: ## Data Structure Reference
253: 
254: ### Session Object
255: ```json
256: {
257:   "id": "uuid-string",
258:   "started_at": "2025-12-10T10:30:00",
259:   "completed_at": "2025-12-10T10:35:00",
260:   "dry_run": false,
261:   "total_files": 1000,
262:   "organized_count": 980,
263:   "skipped_count": 15,
264:   "error_count": 5,
265:   "total_cost": 2.45,
266:   "processing_time": 300.5,
267:   "source_directories": ["/Users/name/Downloads"],
268:   "base_path": "/Users/name/Documents",
269:   "categories": {
270:     "GameAssets": 800,
