<file path="docs/DEPENDENCIES.md">
  1: # Dependencies Guide
  2: 
  3: Complete guide to dependencies for the Schema.org File Organization System.
  4: 
  5: ## Quick Install
  6: 
  7: ```bash
  8: # Create virtual environment
  9: python3 -m venv venv
 10: source venv/bin/activate
 11: 
 12: # Install all Python dependencies
 13: pip install -r requirements.txt
 14: 
 15: # Install system dependencies (macOS)
 16: brew install tesseract poppler
 17: ```
 18: 
 19: ## Dependency Groups
 20: 
 21: ### Core Dependencies (Required)
 22: 
 23: | Package | Version | Purpose |
 24: |---------|---------|---------|
 25: | `Pillow` | >=12.0.0 | Image loading, EXIF extraction, thumbnails |
 26: | `pillow-heif` | >=1.1.1 | HEIC/HEIF support (iPhone photos) |
 27: | `piexif` | >=1.1.3 | EXIF metadata read/write |
 28: | `pytesseract` | >=0.3.13 | OCR text extraction |
 29: | `geopy` | >=2.4.1 | GPS coordinate to location name lookup |
 30: | `SQLAlchemy` | >=2.0.0 | Database storage for file metadata |
 31: 
 32: **Without these:** Basic file organization still works, but metadata extraction and smart classification are disabled.
 33: 
 34: ### AI/ML Dependencies (Recommended)
 35: 
 36: | Package | Version | Purpose |
 37: |---------|---------|---------|
 38: | `torch` | >=2.9.0 | PyTorch deep learning framework |
 39: | `torchvision` | >=0.24.0 | Computer vision utilities |
 40: | `transformers` | >=4.57.0 | Hugging Face CLIP model |
 41: | `huggingface-hub` | >=0.36.0 | Model downloading |
 42: | `opencv-python` | >=4.12.0 | Image processing |
 43: 
 44: **Without these:** No AI-powered content classification. Falls back to keyword-only detection.
 45: 
 46: ### Document Processing (Optional)
 47: 
 48: | Package | Version | Purpose |
 49: |---------|---------|---------|
 50: | `python-docx` | >=1.2.0 | Microsoft Word parsing |
 51: | `pypdf` | >=6.3.0 | PDF text extraction |
 52: | `PyPDF2` | >=3.0.1 | PDF utilities (legacy) |
 53: | `pdf2image` | >=1.17.0 | PDF to image conversion |
 54: | `openpyxl` | >=3.1.5 | Excel spreadsheet parsing |
 55: | `lxml` | >=6.0.0 | XML/HTML parsing |
 56: 
 57: **Without these:** Document metadata extraction limited to filename analysis.
 58: 
 59: ### System Dependencies
 60: 
 61: #### macOS
 62: ```bash
 63: brew install tesseract    # OCR engine (required for pytesseract)
 64: brew install poppler      # PDF rendering (required for pdf2image)
 65: ```
 66: 
 67: #### Linux (Ubuntu/Debian)
 68: ```bash
 69: sudo apt-get install tesseract-ocr
 70: sudo apt-get install poppler-utils
 71: ```
 72: 
 73: #### Windows
 74: - Tesseract: Download from [GitHub releases](https://github.com/UB-Mannheim/tesseract/wiki)
 75: - Poppler: Download from [poppler releases](https://github.com/osber/poppler-windows/releases)
 76: 
 77: ## Feature Availability Matrix
 78: 
 79: | Feature | Required Packages | Fallback Behavior |
 80: |---------|-------------------|-------------------|
 81: | Image metadata | Pillow, piexif | Filename only |
 82: | HEIC photos | pillow-heif | Skip HEIC files |
 83: | OCR text extraction | pytesseract + tesseract | No text from images |
 84: | AI content classification | torch, transformers | Keyword matching only |
 85: | Location from GPS | geopy | No location names |
 86: | Database storage | SQLAlchemy | JSON file storage |
 87: | Word documents | python-docx | Skip .docx files |
 88: | PDF text | pypdf, pdf2image | Skip PDF content |
 89: | Excel files | openpyxl | Skip .xlsx files |
 90: 
 91: ## Health Check
 92: 
 93: Run the built-in health check to verify all dependencies:
 94: 
 95: ```bash
 96: # Activate virtual environment
 97: source venv/bin/activate
 98: 
 99: # Check all dependencies
100: python3 scripts/file_organizer_content_based.py --check-deps
101: 
102: # Or run standalone
103: python3 src/health_check.py -v
104: ```
105: 
106: Example output:
107: ```
108: ============================================================
109: SYSTEM HEALTH CHECK
110: ============================================================
111:   [OK] Python v3.14.0
112:   [OK] Pillow (Image Processing) v12.0.0
113:   [OK] HEIC Support v1.1.1
114:   [OK] OCR (Tesseract) v5.5.1
115:   [OK] AI Vision (CLIP) vtorch 2.9.1, transformers 4.57.3
116:   [OK] Database (SQLAlchemy) v2.0.44
117:   [OK] Geocoding (geopy) v2.4.1
118:   [OK] Document Processing vdocx, pypdf, openpyxl
119: ------------------------------------------------------------
120: Features available: 8/8
121: All features operational!
122: ============================================================
123: ```
124: 
125: ## Minimal Installation
126: 
127: For basic file organization without AI features:
128: 
129: ```bash
130: pip install Pillow pillow-heif piexif pytesseract geopy SQLAlchemy
131: brew install tesseract
132: ```
133: 
134: This gives you:
135: - Image metadata extraction
136: - HEIC support
137: - OCR text extraction
138: - Location lookup
139: - Database storage
140: 
141: ## Full Installation
142: 
143: For all features including AI classification:
144: 
145: ```bash
146: pip install -r requirements.txt
147: brew install tesseract poppler
148: ```
149: 
150: ## Troubleshooting
151: 
152: ### "tesseract not found"
153: ```bash
154: # macOS
155: brew install tesseract
156: 
157: # Verify installation
158: which tesseract
159: tesseract --version
160: ```
161: 
162: ### "No module named 'torch'"
163: ```bash
164: # Install PyTorch (CPU version for smaller download)
165: pip install torch torchvision --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cpu
166: 
167: # Or full version with CUDA support
168: pip install torch torchvision
169: ```
170: 
171: ### "HEIC files not loading"
172: ```bash
173: pip install pillow-heif
174: 
175: # Verify in Python
176: python3 -c "from pillow_heif import register_heif_opener; print('HEIC OK')"
177: ```
178: 
179: ### "PDF conversion failed"
180: ```bash
181: # Install poppler
182: brew install poppler  # macOS
183: sudo apt-get install poppler-utils  # Linux
184: 
185: # Verify
186: which pdftoppm
187: ```
188: 
189: ### Checking installed versions
190: ```bash
191: pip freeze | grep -E "Pillow|torch|transformers|SQLAlchemy"
192: ```
193: 
194: ## Upgrade Dependencies
195: 
196: ```bash
197: # Upgrade all packages
198: pip install --upgrade -r requirements.txt
199: 
200: # Upgrade specific package
201: pip install --upgrade torch transformers
202: ```
203: 
204: ## Development Dependencies
205: 
206: For running tests and code quality tools:
207: 
208: ```bash
209: pip install pytest pytest-cov black flake8 mypy
210: ```
211: 
212: ## Storage Requirements
213: 
214: | Component | Disk Space |
215: |-----------|------------|
216: | Base packages | ~100 MB |
217: | PyTorch (CPU) | ~500 MB |
218: | PyTorch (CUDA) | ~2 GB |
219: | CLIP model (cached) | ~600 MB |
220: | Tesseract data | ~30 MB |
221: 
222: **Total (full install):** ~1.2 GB minimum
223: 
224: ## Python Version
225: 
226: - **Minimum:** Python 3.8
227: - **Recommended:** Python 3.11+
228: - **Tested on:** Python 3.14.0
</file>

