 1: # Schema.org File Organization System
 2: 
 3: AI-powered file organization using CLIP vision, OCR, Schema.org metadata, and entity detection.
 4: 
 5: ## Quick Start
 6: 
 7: ```bash
 8: source venv/bin/activate
 9: organize-files content --source ~/Downloads --dry-run --limit 100
10: organize-files health                    # Check dependencies
11: ```
12: 
13: ## CLI Commands
14: 
15: | Command | Description |
16: |---------|-------------|
17: | `organize-files content` | AI-powered organization (CLIP, OCR) |
18: | `organize-files name` | Filename pattern organization (no AI) |
19: | `organize-files type` | Extension-based organization |
20: | `organize-files health` | Check system dependencies |
21: | `organize-files migrate-ids` | Run database migration |
22: | `organize-files update-site` | Update dashboard data |
23: 
24: ## Project Structure
25: 
26: ```
27: ├── src/                    # Core library
28: │   ├── cli.py              # Unified CLI entry point
29: │   ├── generators.py       # Schema.org metadata generation
30: │   ├── error_tracking.py   # Sentry integration
31: │   └── storage/
32: │       └── graph_store.py  # SQLAlchemy graph with canonical IDs
33: ├── scripts/
34: │   ├── shared/                          # Shared utilities (clip, db, ocr, file ops)
35: │   ├── file_organizer_content_based.py  # Main AI organizer
36: │   ├── image_content_renamer.py         # CLIP-based image renaming
37: │   └── image_content_analyzer.py        # Image content analysis
38: ├── tests/
39: │   ├── unit/               # Unit tests (pytest)
40: │   └── e2e/                # E2E tests (Playwright + OpenTelemetry)
41: ├── _site/                  # Dashboard UI
42: └── results/                # Reports & database
43: ```
44: 
45: **Note on `scripts/shared/`:** Scripts must be run from the project root (or with `scripts/` on `sys.path`) so that `from shared.x import y` resolves correctly. The `organize-files` CLI entry point handles this automatically.
46: 
47: ## Classification Priority
48: 
49: 1. **Organization Detection** - client, vendor, invoice, company names
50: 2. **Person Detection** - resume, contact, signatures (OCR-enhanced)
51: 3. **Legal/Contract** - contracts, agreements, terms
52: 4. **E-commerce/Shopping** - product listings, carts
53: 5. **Software UI** - app interfaces, dashboards
54: 6. **Game Assets** - 200+ patterns, sprites, textures, audio
55: 7. **Filepath Matching** - directory structure patterns
56: 8. **Content Analysis** - OCR text and CLIP vision
57: 9. **MIME Type Fallback** - file extension
58: 
59: ## Output Folders
60: 
61: ```
62: ~/Documents/
63: ├── Organization/{CompanyName}/    # Vendor/partner files
64: ├── Person/{PersonName}/           # Person-related files
65: ├── GameAssets/                    # Sprites, textures, models
66: ├── Financial/                     # Invoices, receipts
67: ├── Technical/                     # Code, configs
68: └── Media/                         # Photos, videos, audio
69: ```
70: 
71: ## Environment
72: 
73: | Variable | Description |
74: |----------|-------------|
75: | `FILE_SYSTEM_SENTRY_DSN` | Sentry error tracking (Doppler) |
76: | `--sentry-dsn` | CLI override |
77: 
78: ## Dependencies
79: 
80: ```bash
81: pip install -e ".[all]" && brew install tesseract poppler
82: ```
83: 
84: ## Troubleshooting
85: 
86: | Issue | Solution |
87: |-------|----------|
88: | HEIC fails | `pip install pillow-heif` |
89: | No OCR | `brew install tesseract` |
90: | No AI | `pip install torch transformers` |
